  "prompt_text": "Solve: If 3x + 2y = 12 and x - y = 1, find x and y. Show your work.",
  "response_text": "To solve the system of equations given by:\n\n1. \\(3x + 2y = 12\\)\n2. \\(x - y = 1\\)\n\nwe can use the method of substitution or elimination. Here, we'll use the substitution method for clarity.\n\nFirst, let's solve the second equation for \\(x\\):\n\n\\[x - y = 1 \\implies x = y + 1\\]\n\nNext, substitute \\(x = y + 1\\) into the first equation:\n\n\\[3(y + 1) + 2y = 12\\]\n\nNow, distribute and combine like terms:\n\n\\[3y + 3 + 2y = 12\\]\n\\[5y + 3 = 12\\]\n\nSubtract 3 from both sides:\n\n\\[5y = 9\\]\n\nDivide by 5:\n\n\\[y = \\frac{9}{5}\\]\n\nNow that we have \\(y\\), substitute it back into the expression for \\(x\\):\n\n\\[x = y + 1 = \\frac{9}{5} + 1 = \\frac{9}{5} + \\frac{5}{5} = \\frac{14}{5}\\]\n\nSo, the solution to the system of equations is:\n\n\\[x = \\frac{14}{5}, \\quad y = \\frac{9}{5}\\]\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 9\nQ (Query Interpretation): 10\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 6\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
